n commodification. In so doing, he offers a new theory of art that prompts a rethinking of the relationship between art, critical theory, and capitalism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Sep 2020) 0aArt and businessxHistoryy21st century. 0aArt and societyxHistoryy21st century. 0aArt, Moderny21st centuryxEconomic aspects. 0aArtsxPolitical aspects. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Semiotics & Theory.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK eBook-Package 2019z978311069632540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478002673zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478002673423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781478002673.jpg  a978-3-11-069632-5  DUK eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles